12.3 Practice
================

1.In the **Practice** interface

. Read step 1 of **File Systems in the Cloud**
. Read **CONCEPT**
. Select **START LAB**
. Select the arrow to the right to see the next steps


.. image:: pictures/practice_lab.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px

2.In the **Practice** interface

. Read step 2 of **File Systems in the Cloud**
. Read **CONCEPT**
. Select **Open AWS Console**
. Select the arrow to the right to see the next steps


.. image:: pictures/open_aws_console.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px


3.In the **AWS Console interface**

. Find **EC2**
. Select **EC2


.. image:: pictures/ec2.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px

4.In the **Practice** interface

. Read step 3 of **File Systems in the Cloud**
. Read **CONCEPT**
. Select the arrow to the right to see the next steps


.. image:: pictures/concept.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px


5.In the **EC2** interface

. Select **Instances**
. View instances


.. image:: pictures/instances.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px


6.In the **Practice** interface

. Read step 5 of **File Systems in the Cloud**
. Read **CONCEPT**
. Select the arrow to the right to see the next steps


.. image:: pictures/concept_2.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px


7.In the **EC2** interface

. View the Availability Zone
. Select Security Groups


.. image:: pictures/Availability_Zone.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px

8.In the **Practice** interface

. Read step 6 of **File Systems in the Cloud**
. Read **CONCEPT**
. Select the arrow to the right to see the next steps


.. image:: pictures/ concept_3.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px

9.In the **Security Groups** interface

. View **Web Server Security Group**
. Select **Create security group**


.. image:: pictures/Security_Groups.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px

10.In the **Praccticce interface**

. Read step 7 of **File Systems in the Cloud**
. Read **CONCEPT**
. Select the arrow to the right to see the next steps


.. image:: pictures/Pracctice.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px

11.In the **Create security** group interface

. **Security group name**, enter PetModels-EFS-1-SG
. **Description**, enter Restrict access to webservers only
. Select **VPC PetModels**
. Select **Add rule**


.. image:: pictures/security.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px

12.In the **Practice interface**

. Read step 8 of **File Systems in the Cloud**
. Read **CONCEPT**
. Select the arrow to the right to see the next steps


.. image:: pictures/practice_1.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px

13.In the **Create security group** interface

. In **Inbound rules**, select **NFS**
. Select **Security group**, select **webserver**


.. image:: pictures/nfs.png
   :align: center
   :width: 700px

